The paper discusses the role of Open Access publishing in science management and research policy, which is relevant to the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The methodology presented in the paper involves creating OA labels for publications, which could be relevant to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper mentions open data, which is relevant to the field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
